Privacy and Cookies Policy
Please read carefully
This document is about how Six Butterball respects your privacy when you use or play any of the following services:
(i) any of our online or mobile games, products or services, including mobile applications on iOS, Android and any other applicable mobile platform; and
(ii) any of our games, products or services (including support services) which may be accessible via a web application, third party platform or social networking service (including Facebook).
We’ll call them together our “Services“. By using any of our Services, you confirm that you have read, understood and agree to this privacy and cookies policy (“policy”). If you do not agree to this policy, please do not use any of the Services. If you have any queries, please email us at
l261991282@foxmail.com
. We may change this policy at any time in which case we shall notify you of any changes to this policy by noting this on our Sites or otherwise within our Services. The changes will apply to your use of our Services after we have given notice. If you do not wish to accept the new policy you should not continue to use the Services. If you continue to use the Services after the date on which the change comes into effect, your use of the Services indicates your agreement to be bound by the new policy.
Introduction
1.1 Six Butterball are committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. This policy sets out the basis on which we will process information we collect from you, or that you provide to us. This includes personal information (meaning information which, on its own or in combination with other information, can be used to identify you) and non-personal information. Please read this policy carefully so that you understand how we will treat your information.
A quick word about children
We recognise we have a special obligation to protect personal information obtained from children. We do not and will not knowingly collect information from any unsupervised child under the age of 13. For children under the age of 13 wishing to use the Services, written permission or other verifiable consent is required from a parent or guardian (details of which can be obtained from
l261991282@foxmail.com
)
. In some countries, prior written permission or other verifiable consent may be also required from a parent or guardian for children under 18 years of age, as indicated in our Terms of Service.
3. Information we may collect from you
3.1 We respect your right to privacy and will only process personal information you provide to us in accordance with the GDPR, the Privacy and Electronic Communications (EC Directive) Regulations 2003 and other applicable privacy laws.
3.2 The kinds of information which we may process include:
(a) Your name;
(b) Your email address;
(c) Your user name, ‘high score’ name or any other name used to identify yourself in any Services;
(d) Technical or other details about any device which you use to access the Services, including: Internet and/or network connection (including your IP address); your Media Access Control (MAC); your device Unique Device Identifier (UDID) or equivalent; your operating system, browser type or other software; your hardware or mobile device details (including your mobile device type and number and mobile carrier details); or other technical details;
(e) Details of your use of our Services including, but not limited to: metrics information about when and how you use the Services; traffic data; and your geographical location data;
(f) Details about your use of social networking and our Services. This includes certain information from Facebook (including access to your friends list as well as aggregated non-personal analytics data about our users) in accordance with Facebook’s terms and conditions; and
(g) Other personal or business information required in order to help you with any queries or support matters you may need assistance with via our forums or customer support service.
4. How we collect information:
4.1 We may collect and process information about you through the following means:
Contact Information submitted via our Sites in relation to a potential job:
We often advertise jobs on our Sites and any information you choose to provide us will be used to assess you as a candidate and undertake criminal record and/or checks with references. If you subsequently join us as an employee, we may create a file in respect of your employment which shall be kept secure and only used for purposes relating to your employment. We will, however, provide you with further details on this at the time of you becoming an employee.
Account Information:
Personal information that you supply when creating an account to use our Online Services e.g., our support forums (namely your date of birth, e-mail address and username (which may or may not be personal information depending on the username that you choose));
User Support Information:
If you contact us for technical or customer support, we will keep a record of your name, contact details (such as email address or telephone number), a record of your call and/or correspondence along with a note of the games or issues relevant to your call.
Contests, Surveys & Promotions Information:
If you enter any of our on-line contests, promotions or loyalty programs, we will collect personal information (such as your name, email address, postal address, birthday and contact phone numbers) in order to register you in the contest, promotion or loyalty program.
Technical and Usage Information when browsing our Sites:
When you access and use our Sites, we collect technical information such as details about your computer system and details of your use of the Sites including, but not limited to, traffic data, location data, weblogs and other communication data and the resources that you access such as server log files and tracking technologies including cookies, IP addresses, browser information, the date and time spent on our Sites and other similar information. Some of this information is collected through Google Analytics. We may be able to use IP addresses to personally identify you to enforce our Terms of Service and/or block certain IP addresses from our Sites if we believe that there has been misuse of our Sites. We may obtain information about your general internet usage by using a cookie file which is stored on the hard drive of your computer. Cookies contain information that is transferred to your computer’s hard drive. They help us to improve our Sites and to deliver a better and more personalised service. They enable us:
To estimate our audience size and usage pattern.
To store information about your preferences, and so allow us to customise our Sites according to your individual interests.
To speed up your searches.
To recognise you when you return to our Sites.
Personal information received from a Mobile Device:
When you access our Services as an “app” or “application” through a mobile device, we collect your unique device identifier, various information collected via the use of certain SDKs and other similar technologies as indicated in paragraph 6, and other device identifier and technical information such as your Google Play ID or Game Centre ID.
5.Cookies
Cookies are files with a small amount of data that are commonly used as anonymous unique identifiers. These are sent to your browser from the websites that you visit and are stored on your device's internal memory.
This Service does not use these “cookies” explicitly. However, the app may use third party code and libraries that use “cookies” to collect information and improve their services. You have the option to either accept or refuse these cookies and know when a cookie is being sent to your device. If you choose to refuse our cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of this Service.
