How We Use Personal Information
6.1 The information collected above may be used by us as follows:
Contact Information submitted via our Sites
in relation to a potential job:
We use this information to assess you as a candidate and undertake criminal record and/or checks with references.
Account Information:
We use this information to verify your identity and allow you to access the features of our Services that require such account registration (such as our support forums).
c.
User Support Information:
We use this information to respond to the particular support query that you have raised.
Contests & Promotions Information:
We use this information to ensure that you are entered into the contest/promotion and to let you know if you are a winner.
Technical and Usage Information (including Cookies information):
We use this information to monitor and analyse traffic to our Sites, to improve our Sites, to personalise your experience on our Sites, to resolve technical problems with our Sites and to report aggregate information to our advertisers
Personal information received from a Mobile Device:
We use this to identify you as a player and to allow you to play our games, as well as to improve the functionality and service of our games. Where you give your consent, we also use the information collected via the use of certain SDKs and other similar technologies as indicated in paragraph 6 to serve targeted adverts to you, as opposed to adverts that may not be of interest to you.
7
. Grounds For Processing
7.1 We rely on the following processing grounds to collect and use the above listed information:
Contact Information submitted via our Sites in relation to a potential job:
We rely either on legal obligation or legitimate interests depending on what information you supply to us. Some information will be required in order for us to fulfil our duties under applicable employment legislation, other information will be in our legitimate interests. It is in our legitimate interests and necessary to collect such items of personal information because this is necessary in order to assess whether you are a suitable candidate for our team. The items of personal information collected and for which we rely on legitimate interests, are not of a nature whereby your rights and freedoms as a data subject are outweighed by such data collection.
Account Information:
For the information that you submit to create an account that is not mandatory, we rely on consent. It is your choice as to whether to supply such information and you can still have an account without it. For the information that you supply that is mandatory, we rely on legitimate interests as it is in our legitimate interests and necessary to collect such information in order to create an appropriate account and help to e.g., ensure that you are who you say you are and not abusing the use of our support forums for example. The items of personal information collected and for which we rely on legitimate interests, are not of a nature whereby your rights and freedoms as a data subject are outweighed by such data collection.
User Support Information:
We rely on legitimate interests to collect this information as it is in our legitimate interests and necessary to collect such information in order to be able to respond to your support query in the most efficient way possible. The items of personal information collected and for which we rely on legitimate interests, are not of a nature whereby your rights and freedoms as a data subject are outweighed by such data collection.
Contests & Promotions Information:
We rely on consent to collect this information as it is your choice as to whether to participate in such contest or promotion.
Technical and Usage Information (including Cookies information):
We rely on legitimate interests to collect this information as it is in our legitimate interests and necessary to collect such information in order to be able to carry out the technical support and management of our Sites that we need to do to make them run as efficiently as possible. The items of personal information collected and for which we rely on legitimate interests, are not of a nature whereby your rights and freedoms as a data subject are outweighed by such data collection.
Personal information received from a Social Networking Site (“SNS”):
We rely on legitimate interests to collect this information as it is in our legitimate interests and necessary to collect such information in order to allow you to sign-in to and use our games and make the game playing experience as efficient as possible. The items of personal information collected and for which we rely on legitimate interests, are not of a nature whereby your rights and freedoms as a data subject are outweighed by such data collection. The only time we rely on consent is in relation to the use of your e-mail collected via the SNS where we obtain your consent where required under applicable direct marketing legislation to send you appropriate information about products and services that we consider you may be interested in.
Personal information received from a Mobile Device:
With the exception of where we use such information to serve targeted adverts (where we rely on consent), we rely on legitimate interests to collect this information as it is in our legitimate interests and necessary to collect such information in order to be able to carry out the technical support and management of our games that we need to do to make them run as efficiently as possible. The items of personal information collected and for which we rely on legitimate interests, are not of a nature whereby your rights and freedoms as a data subject are outweighed by such data collection.
Promotional purposes:
We rely on legitimate interests except where we need to rely on consent under direct marketing legislation.
Chat services:
We rely on consent as it is your choice as to whether to participate in the chat services.
8. Where we store your personal information, how it is kept secure and how long we store it for
8.1 The information that we collect from you may be transferred to, stored and processed at a destination outside the European Economic Area (“EEA”) (including the USA). It may also be processed by staff operating outside the EEA who work for us or for one of our suppliers. Such staff maybe engaged in, among other things, the provision of support services and the processing of your payment details. Where we transfer your personal information outside the EEA we have put in place appropriate adequacy procedures to ensure that such transfers are GDPR compliant. We will take all steps reasonably necessary to ensure that your information is treated securely and in accordance with this policy.
8.2 If you have a password which enables you to access certain parts of our Sites, you are responsible for keeping this password confidential. Please don’t share it with anyone.
8.3 All information you provide to us is stored on our secure servers. Unfortunately, the transmission of information via the Internet is not completely secure. Although we will do our best to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee the security of your data transmitted to our servers via any of our Services; any transmission is at your own risk. Once we have received your information, we will use strict procedures and security features to try to prevent unauthorised access.
8.4 We retain your personal information in accordance with our retention policy – if this is obtained in relation to you applying for a job, for 2 years after you end your employment with us, and if this is obtained in relation to you using any of our Services, for 2 years after your last active session. We will, however, retain a copy of your player save file for 6 years because this doesn’t contain any personal information and allows you to reactivate the game in question with your last progress applied should you wish to do so.
8.5 Please remember that any communications you have via our Services, including for example our games, may reveal your screen name, other details about you and the content of any communications by you to other users. We are not responsible for the activities of other users or other third parties whom you choose to provide your information to or otherwise interact with (whether via our Services or otherwise)
9. Disclosure of your information
9.1 We may disclose your personal information to any member of our group, which means our subsidiaries, our ultimate holding company and its subsidiaries, as defined in section 1159 of the UK Companies Act 2006.
9.2 We may disclose your personal information to third parties:
(a) In the event that we sell or buy any business or assets, in which case we may disclose your personal information to the prospective seller or buyer of such business or assets.
(b) If we or substantially all of our assets are acquired by a third party, in which case personal information held by us about our customers will be one of the transferred assets.
(c) If we are under a duty to disclose or share your personal information in order to comply with any legal obligation, or in order to enforce and other agreements; or to protect our rights, property, or safety of our customers or others.
9.3 We may also share your non-personal information with third party partners who work with us to provide the Services to you (for example, third party developers who we’ve worked with to create one of our games). These include service providers assisting us with: (i) ad mediation; (ii) ad monetization; (iii) hosting and storing the information that we collect; (iv) providing support services; (v) marketing and mail campaigns; (vi) payment processing; and (vii) website analytics. The type of information that we provide to such service providers depends on the nature of the service that they are providing e.g., we would pass your contact information to receive a newsletter to our marketing and mail campaign service providers, we would pass your user support information to our support services provider, and we use certain third party processors to collect various items of information that comprise the Technical and Usage Information (as detailed more particularly in paragraph 6 above).
10. Third party sites
Our Services may, from time to time, contain links to and from the websites or services of partner networks, advertisers and affiliates. If you follow a link to any of these websites, please note that these websites or services may have their own privacy policies and that we do not accept any responsibility or liability for these policies, nor do we endorse such websites or services. Please check carefully before you submit any personal information to these websites or services
11. Push notifications and local notifications
We may, with your consent, send push or local notifications to your mobile device to provide game updates and other relevant messages. You can manage push and local notifications from the Options or Settings section within the relevant game. You may also be able to manage them from your device’s settings section for the relevant game.
12. Your rights
You can contact us using the details set out in paragraph 15 below if you wish to: (a) access a copy of the personal information that we hold about you; (b) correct any items of personal information that we hold about you; and/or (c) have any items of personal information that we hold about you erased or object to our processing of such items of personal information.
13. Changes to our privacy and cookies policy
Any changes we may make to this policy in the future will be posted on this page and, where appropriate, notified to you by e-mail.
14. Contact
We welcome any questions, comments and requests regarding this policy, which should be addressed to
